LIMPOPO-based company Merwalo Tourism and Associates has joined hands with the Limpopo Indie Film Festival to promote the province. Merwalo Tourism and Associates CEO Jonas Ngake said: “The festival will run from 21 March until 25 March in Polokwane, streaming films back to back and giving workshops. “It will end with an award for film-makers. “Film-makers can expect the presence of big names in the film industry that includes Bonginhlahla Ncube and international award-winning producer and director, Mr B.” Mr B directed and produced 48 Hours and Safe Bet, which were shown on Fly Emirate, Ster-Kinekor, Showmax, Turkish Airlines, Kenya Airways, Kwese TV, Berlin and Germany. ALSO READ : LONDON WATCH OUT, HERE COME CELESTE AND THENJIWE! “Bonginhlahla will facilitate a two-day directing workshop. “Kgopotso Mashile, a young female filmmaker and entrepreneur from Pretoria, will facilitate a scriptwriting workshop, while Ntando Mhlanga, a Tshwane University of Technology graduate and assistant costume designer, will close the workshop sessions with a make-up and costume workshop,” said Ngake. He said the festival is open to all developing film-makers, irrespective of gender or language of use in films. “All films shot in vernacular languages must be translated to English,” he said.